Mario, also crafted from clay, stands awkwardly at the beginning of the level, his rounded limbs and uneven mustache giving him a playful, clumsy look. The pipes, coins, and Goombas are similarly rough and imperfect, adding to the charm of the scene. The game’s interface is visible, with a classic score counter at the top left, “MARIO” written in blocky letters, along with a coin count and timer ticking down in the right-hand corner. The whole level has an endearing, low-quality feel, blending the nostalgic pixel art with the tactile, squishy texture of clay animation.

A side-scrolling Mario game level made entirely from lumpy, handcrafted clay. The pixelated 8-bit world has been transformed into squishy, uneven textures, with every element—from the ground to the iconic question blocks—sculpted from multicolored clay. Mario, also crafted from clay, stands awkwardly at the beginning of the level, his rounded limbs and uneven mustache giving him a playful, clumsy look. The pipes, coins, and Goombas are similarly rough and imperfect, adding to the charm of the scene. The game’s interface is visible, with a classic score counter at the top left, “MARIO” written in blocky letters, along with a coin count and timer ticking down in the right-hand corner. The whole level has an endearing, low-quality feel, blending the nostalgic pixel art with the tactile, squishy texture of clay animation.
